sequenceDiagram
    participant "Frontend SPA (Vendor's Browser)" as FrontendSPAVendorsBrowser
    participant "Backend API" as BackendAPI
    participant "PostgreSQL Database" as PostgreSQLDatabase
    participant "AWS SES" as AWSSES
    participant "Frontend SPA (Admin's Browser)" as FrontendSPAAdminsBrowser

    activate BackendAPI
    FrontendSPAVendorsBrowser->>BackendAPI: 1. Submit Question for Project
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPAVendorsBrowser: 201 Created | Question ID
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 1.1. Persist New Question
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: New Question Record
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 1.2. Fetch Admin Contact for Notification
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Admin User Email
    BackendAPI->>AWSSES: 1.3. Send 'New Question' Notification
    FrontendSPAAdminsBrowser->>BackendAPI: 2. Submit Answer to Question
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPAAdminsBrowser: 200 OK | Updated Q&A Object
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 2.1. Update Question with Answer
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Updated Question Record
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 2.2. Fetch All Invited Vendors for Project
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: List of Vendor Emails
    BackendAPI->>AWSSES: 2.3. LOOP: Send 'New Answer' Notification

    note over FrontendSPAVendorsBrowser: Vendor enters question in a textarea within the <QandA> component. On submit, UI state is set to ...
    note over FrontendSPAVendorsBrowser: On receiving a '201 Created' response, the UI updates to show the submitted question with a 'Pend...
    note over FrontendSPAAdminsBrowser: Admin is notified (e.g., email) and navigates to the project management workspace. The UI fetches...
    note over FrontendSPAAdminsBrowser: Admin types an answer. On submit, the UI enters a 'saving' state. On '200 OK' response, the UI up...

    deactivate BackendAPI
